Why don’t you smoke inside?

236
00:13:27.556 --> 00:13:29.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s all right. Just one cigarette.

237
00:13:30.601 --> 00:13:33.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don’t wanna be hated
by the princess in your tummy.

238
00:13:34.605 --> 00:13:38.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It was really nice taking a bath together.

239
00:13:38.442 --> 00:13:41.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It resolves the lack of communication
we’ve had.

240
00:13:41.862 --> 00:13:43.322 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let’s take a bath together again, okay?

241
00:13:43.405 --> 00:13:46.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You like doing it in small spaces?

242
00:13:46.450 --> 00:13:49.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You’ve gotta tell me
these important things.

243
00:14:17.439 --> 00:14:18.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
SHIN

244
00:14:22.862 --> 00:14:24.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, hello. Hachi?

245
00:14:26.323 --> 00:14:27.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm.

246
00:14:27.658 --> 00:14:29.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry for calling this late.

247
00:14:29.869 --> 00:14:31.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have to go to work
early tomorrow too, right?

248
00:14:34.915 --> 00:14:36.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

249
00:14:36.292 --> 00:14:38.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I’m not calling</i>
<i>about anything in particular.</i>

250
00:14:38.586 --> 00:14:40.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It’s just that I haven’t seen you</i>
<i>since the fireworks</i>

251
00:14:40.462 --> 00:14:41.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and was wondering how you’re doing.</i>

252
00:14:42.798 --> 00:14:45.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The fireworks were fun, huh?</i>

253
00:14:45.175 --> 00:14:48.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That was the first time</i>
<i>I had ever lit fireworks.</i>

254
00:14:49.513 --> 00:14:53.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We wrote wishes on tanabata, too,</i>
<i>this summer.</i>

255
00:14:53.350 --> 00:14:55.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Everything was so much fun.</i>

256
00:14:58.522 --> 00:15:02.151 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let’s light fireworks with everyone again.

257
00:15:02.234 --> 00:15:04.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you think they still sell them
at the convenience store?

258
00:15:09.450 --> 00:15:10.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m sorry, Shin.

259
00:15:10.951 --> 00:15:12.161 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What for?

260
00:15:13.537 --> 00:15:15.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Because I’m a traitor.

261
00:15:17.166 --> 00:15:19.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can’t look you guys in the eyes anymore.

262
00:15:24.840 --> 00:15:28.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ll always be on your side,
no matter what, Hachi.

263
00:15:31.388 --> 00:15:33.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nana, where’s the hair dryer?

264
00:15:39.104 --> 00:15:41.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m sorry, Jun-chan. Good night.

265
00:15:41.649 --> 00:15:42.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Found it.

266
00:15:52.451 --> 00:15:56.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What’s wrong? Did Jun-chan lecture
you about something?

267
00:16:01.168 --> 00:16:04.004 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just got a bit homesick.

268
00:16:04.088 --> 00:16:06.006 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
SEPTEMBER 10
8:32 P.M. HACHI

269
00:16:06.882 --> 00:16:09.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Don’t you ever mention that name again.</i>

270
00:16:09.259 --> 00:16:13.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Even Nobu has a thing or two</i>
<i>he would rather not talk about.</i>

271
00:16:13.138 --> 00:16:14.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
SEPTEMBER 10
8:32 P.M. HACHI

272
00:16:17.184 --> 00:16:19.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So that’s what’s going on.

273
00:16:29.613 --> 00:16:32.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Because I’m a traitor.</i>

274
00:16:33.492 --> 00:16:36.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I can’t look you guys in the eyes anymore.</i>

275
00:16:37.746 --> 00:16:42.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I believe people are bound by trust.</i>

276
00:16:46.964 --> 00:16:48.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I’m sorry.</i>

277
00:16:49.008 --> 00:16:51.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Please give me Yasu’s cell number.</i>

278
00:16:52.386 --> 00:16:54.847 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Reira was in love with Takumi.</i>

279
00:16:56.640 --> 00:17:00.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Looking back, I know it was</i>
<i>just petty jealousy…</i>

280
00:17:01.186 --> 00:17:04.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Yet I couldn’t support her</i>
<i>when she needed me the most.</i>

281
00:17:05.899 --> 00:17:09.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But can't you support her now, Yasu?</i>

282
00:17:10.821 --> 00:17:14.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Right now, my hands are full</i>
<i>taking care of you guys.</i>

283
00:17:18.287 --> 00:17:19.204 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shin!

284
00:17:19.288 --> 00:17:20.497 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ren, you’re here!

285
00:17:20.581 --> 00:17:21.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You…

286
00:17:21.832 --> 00:17:23.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hate to say this
since I haven’t seen you in a while,

287
00:17:23.542 --> 00:17:27.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I have to leave again
right away. Sorry.

288
00:17:27.546 --> 00:17:29.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can’t you at least be a little sorry?

289
00:17:29.590 --> 00:17:33.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
